rComments: Her assignments are never clear and her communication with the grading assistant seemed minimal. Pro tip with this prof: "Things to consider" translates to "Things that are MANDATORY," apparently. I needed to keep my GPA above 3 this semester, but now that seems impossible.

I love this prof, and honestly, she is one of the best and hard-working profs at UTSC. She creates a welcoming environment and a safe space where students can share their ideas freely. Study her lecture notes and participate in class discussions and you will be good!

I took this class Women, gender and Islam and as non- Muslim woman I learned so many things. The class is super interesting and I recommend it to everyone. She is an amazing prof, I like the way she teaches and the course materials are very helpful and engaging. iIdefinlty recommend taking her courses.

You need to be hardworking and keep up with the readings. Obviously, when you participate in class you showcase your knowledge and understanding of the materials. Her class is full of amazing and new concepts, it is always related to our real lives hence it becomes very interesting to learn. She summarizes everything on her slides so yey!!

This prof is an amazing lecturer and her office is open for questions and feedbacks. as a student, I appreciate her care for students because she does everything to help you if you go and ask for her help. She is very nice and welcoming.

I first took Atiqa's class on women and islam and absolutely loved it. So much so that I am taking another class with her this year! Truly a great and hard-working Professor. If you work hard, you will do well in this class. If your minoring or majoring in Women Studies take one of her classes before you graduate you will not regret it!

For teaching a class that is half women and gender studies she is really anti-feminist. Made for an uncomfortable semester. Speaks way to fast and does not put up her slides half the time. Not a great prof, would not recommend.
